parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of fuel tank welds and resulting debris can cause the fuel system to clog, leading to sudden loss of power, stalling, and potentially catastrophic accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: and engine hesitation; symptoms may occur randomly or periodically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without throttle input
even when the brake is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle response can cause loss of power, stalling, or bogging down, which can lead to accidents, especially when overtaking or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate when the throttle is twisted

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause a loss of speed, leading to hazardous situations, especially when merging onto busy highways or navigating through heavy traffic. This can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine cuts out or stalls
the engine restarts on its own.
